-How much are the tomatoes?
-Twenty centimes.

41
00:05:20,060 --> 00:05:21,891
That's too expensive.

42
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:27,737
I don't have enough money..

43
00:05:52,420 --> 00:05:54,331
Come on, let's go..

44
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:10,890
Oh, those Germans...
I've never seen men like them.

45
00:06:11,100 --> 00:06:12,169
They are well-mannered.

46
00:06:12,540 --> 00:06:15,612
and have blond hair and blue eyes.

47
00:06:16,513 --> 00:06:19,513
Quite frankly, if one approaches me,
I won't let him go.

48
00:06:18,580 --> 00:06:20,332
-Me neither

49
00:06:20,540 --> 00:06:22,531
What did you study at school today?

50
00:06:23,100 --> 00:06:24,514
-Nothing.

51
00:06:24,515 --> 00:06:26,515
She's been expelled!

52
00:06:26,516 --> 00:06:29,016
As if me being fired
wasn't enough!

53
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:32,670
She picked a bad day for it!

54
00:06:33,540 --> 00:06:36,737
-You've got nothing to teach me?
-You know all you need.

55
00:06:36,940 --> 00:06:40,376
You can sew and cook.
Khaled will be happy with that.

56
00:06:50,860 --> 00:06:53,693
-My mother drives me mad.
-So does mine.

57
00:07:00,180 --> 00:07:03,968
Say...
I've wanted to ask for a year now

58
00:07:04,380 --> 00:07:05,972
But I don't dare.

59
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:08,894
Go on.  Say it!

60
00:07:09,540 --> 00:07:11,770
Why did your mother lose her job?

61
00:07:12,740 --> 00:07:14,731
Because of the French...

62
00:07:15,380 --> 00:07:16,779
Why?

63
00:07:17,620 --> 00:07:20,851
I don't know.
They don't like us anymore.

64
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:23,500
Tita!

65
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:26,779
Come here.

66
00:07:31,620 --> 00:07:33,258
I hear you haven't paid?

67
