80
00:08:43,820 --> 00:08:45,173
And you?

81
00:08:46,780 --> 00:08:48,532
I can't sleep.

82
00:08:49,820 --> 00:08:51,333
Me neither.

83
00:08:57,060 --> 00:08:59,210
Want to sleep in my room?

84
00:09:02,020 --> 00:09:03,453
Wait for me.

85
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:07,456
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

86
00:10:07,660 --> 00:10:09,332
Good morning.

87
00:10:58,420 --> 00:10:59,614
Nour?

88
00:11:00,220 --> 00:11:02,097
Come here, my girl!

89
00:11:05,580 --> 00:11:07,696
Take this to Tita.

90
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:18,393
Husband

91
00:11:19,300 --> 00:11:21,131
I wish to talk to you.

92
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:23,752
-What's the matter?

93
00:11:23,753 --> 00:11:26,853
-Khaled want to know
the date about the wedding.

94
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:29,769
-Has he found work?
-No, not yet.

95
00:11:30,540 --> 00:11:32,578
-No work, no wedding!

96
00:11:32,879 --> 00:11:35,879
Come on, he's our cousin!

97
00:11:36,940 --> 00:11:41,172
How will he provide for her?
No work, no wedding.

98
00:11:42,260 --> 00:11:44,376
May God forgive me!

99
00:12:19,580 --> 00:12:21,252
What are they doing?

100
00:12:22,180 --> 00:12:25,650
-They're laughing.  Really?

101
00:12:26,260 --> 00:12:28,728
Come and help me now!

102
00:12:32,980 --> 00:12:34,971
There are dresses in my room.

103
00:12:44,140 --> 00:12:45,759
-Antonietta!

104
00:12:45,760 --> 00:12:47,860
-Yes, dear.

105
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:51,376
I'll sew it
so you can pay the grocer back.

106
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:58,055
-Tita?
-Yes.

107
00:12:58,860 --> 00:13:01,613
-My mum sent this.
-Thank you, Nour.

108
00:13:02,580 --> 00:13:04,172
What's wrong?

109
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:09,573
You haven't turned the radio on
for us this morning?

110
00:13:10,980 --> 00:13:13,050
Come on.

111
00:13:13,620 --> 00:13:15,576
Come with me.

112
00:13:17,260 --> 00:13:20,058
Come let Tita cuddle you.

113
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:30,497
Ah, Nour, the world is cruel.

114
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:40,859
Wait here, I'lll get you
some  Molokheya.

115
00:13:46,620 --> 00:13:48,417
What's wrong?

116
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:52,210
I need your help.
I have to see Khaled.

117
00:13:53,980 --> 00:13:55,129
Can you help me?

118
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:08,570
What's that red dress?

119
00:14:08,571 --> 00:14:11,271
Try it on for the synagogue.
I prefer the blue one.

120
00:14:11,293 --> 00:14:12,899
No, it makes you look pale.

121
00:14:12,900 --> 00:14:14,572
-It doesn't.  -Enough!

122
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:18,137
-Heed my advice to attract Raoul.
-I don't want to.

123
00:14:18,340 --> 00:14:21,059
You'll have to
after what you did at school.

124
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:25,299
Is this a time to sing songs
against Marshall Petain?.

125
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:27,975
Please Nour, tell her to try it on.

126
00:14:30,420 --> 00:14:32,349
It isn't sewn yet!

127
00:14:32,350 --> 00:14:34,250
You can finish it tomorrow.

128
00:14:34,260 --> 00:14:36,535
No time.
I have to work with Nour.

129
00:14:37,660 --> 00:14:39,890
As if the Germans
will let you go back to school?

130
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:42,159
The Allies will.

131
00:14:42,460 --> 00:14:44,815
Sew away
while you wait for them.

132
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:54,488
Our concert today was brought

133
00:14:54,510 --> 00:14:57,609
to you by the Galeries Barbes

134
00:14:57,620 --> 00:15:00,378
and we hope that you enjoyed it.

135
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:03,038
Your satisfaction
is the goal of our store.

136
00:15:03,140 --> 00:15:05,677
For you, we hire
the top music hall stars.

137
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:06,378
For you,

138
00:15:07,180 --> 00:15:10,235
we have developed
our quick-dry wax polish,

139
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:15,200
