wherever they live.

149
00:15:51,231 --> 00:15:55,260
The fine is set at the fair sum
of 20 million francs,

150
00:15:56,580 --> 00:15:59,600
to be paid immediately
to avoid bloody reprisals.

151
00:15:59,601 --> 00:16:01,000
May God destroy them!

152
00:16:01,001 --> 00:16:02,001
Jewry as a whole

153
00:16:02,801 --> 00:16:04,802
is the greatest and staunchest enemy

154
00:16:04,803 --> 00:16:07,503
of our cause and the Third Reich.

155
00:16:11,620 --> 00:16:13,650
Wait in the living room

156
00:16:13,658 --> 00:16:15,658
Thank you.

157
00:16:31,900 --> 00:16:33,538
Do you know Paris?

158
00:16:34,540 --> 00:16:36,849
I studied medicine there.

159
00:16:37,060 --> 00:16:41,850
I stayed until the occupation,
when I had to come back here.

160
00:16:44,420 --> 00:16:45,819
And you,

161
00:16:46,940 --> 00:16:48,373
tell me things.

162
00:16:52,540 --> 00:16:55,179
-What do you like to do?
-Nothing.

163
00:17:06,220 --> 00:17:07,858
Do you like my house?

164
00:17:35,220 --> 00:17:37,211
Not very talkative.

165
00:17:37,820 --> 00:17:40,937
You were more outspoken at school!

166
00:17:41,140 --> 00:17:45,133
How do you know about that?
-The entire city knows.

167
00:18:03,420 --> 00:18:04,455
Go back and see him.

168
00:18:05,140 --> 00:18:07,238
-Be nice to him.

169
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:09,539
I don't want to marry him.

170
00:18:09,540 --> 00:18:12,612
When you're poor,
you can't be choosy.

171
00:18:13,140 --> 00:18:14,971
You eat and stay quiet.

172
00:18:17,940 --> 00:18:20,374
You want me to die in poverty?

173
00:18:32,980 --> 00:18:35,494
This man was sent by God.

174
00:18:36,900 --> 00:18:38,492
He'll bring you fame and joy.

175
00:18:39,740 --> 00:18:43,335
And he'll help us pay the fine.

176
00:18:48,340 --> 00:18:51,616
At first, I too thought
I didn't love your father.

177
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:54,338
And then...

178
00:18:56,060 --> 00:18:57,937
I got to know him.

179
00:19:14,860 --> 00:19:16,691
there's a war on.

180
00:19:29,980 --> 00:19:33,370
Now ask your god about the fine.

181
00:19:35,740 --> 00:19:37,196
<i>"Almighty God,"</i>

182
00:19:37,197 --> 00:19:41,657
<i>"give Myriam  20 million francs
to pay the fine."</i>

183
00:19:44,260 --> 00:19:45,659
We'll See.

184
00:19:46,460 --> 00:19:49,657
If it doesn't work,
you'll have to ask Raoul.

185
00:19:53,740 --> 00:19:56,300
You'll end up liking him one day.

186
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:05,294
No chance of that.

187
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:10,536
And he lives far away!

188
00:20:13,220 --> 00:20:15,051
We won't be able to see each other?

189
00:21:14,420 --> 00:21:16,650
First...

190
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:27,929
First of all...

191
00:24:12,420 --> 00:24:14,138
Have you finished it?

192
00:24:15,060 --> 00:24:17,858
-And the Arabian book?
-That too.

193
00:24:18,940 --> 00:24:20,658
That's good

194
00:24:24,980 --> 00:24:26,971
Have you found work?

195
00:24:28,820 --> 00:24:30,412
Not yet.

196
00:24:30,860 --> 00:24:32,870
You have to, Khaled!

197
00:24:32,900 --> 00:24:34,671
I know.

198
00:24:35,820 --> 00:24:38,578
Why did you want to see me?

199
00:24:38,579 --> 00:24:41,579
My father
wants to call off the marriage.

200
00:24:48,260 --> 00:24:49,739
Don't worry.

201
00:24:50,980 --> 00:24:52,777
I'll soon find work.

202
00:25:20,660 --> 00:25:23,413
I have to go.
Myriam will be worried.

203
00:25:43,460 --> 00:25:46,258
-What's that?
-The Americans.

204
00:26:14,940 --> 00:26:18,250
-This is for you.
- For me?

205
00:26:21,300 --> 00:26:23,147
Think it's my size?

206
00:26:23,148 --> 00:26:24,148
Try it on.

207
00:26:26,580 --> 00:26:28,696
You'll wear it when you see Khaled.

208
00:27:00,180 --> 00:27:03,172
Fits perfectly.
Thank you.

209
00:27:16,020 --> 00:27:18,170
Did you kiss Khaled last time?

210
00:27:19,460 --> 00:27:22,338
-Yes.
-What's it like?

211
00:27:25,020 --> 00:27:26,658
It's scary.

212
00:27:32,020 --> 00:27:36,059
<i>"The bride has blackened her eyelashes"</i>

213
00:27:37,260 --> 00:27:41,219
<i>"and made up her lips"</i>

214
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:45,175
<i>"She has been to the hammam"</i>

215
