the political situation?

263
00:31:51,580 --> 00:31:55,334
No one is fooled by the Nazi propaganda.

264
00:31:55,540 --> 00:31:56,540
Grave?

265
00:31:56,660 --> 00:32:00,096
The Communists have asked me
to contact the Nationalists.

266
00:32:01,180 --> 00:32:03,614
We'd like them to take a stand
against the Axis.

267
00:32:03,820 --> 00:32:05,811
I think they will.

268
00:32:06,500 --> 00:32:09,333
We share the same goal:
independence of the Tunisia.

269
00:32:09,340 --> 00:32:11,159
-I saw Moslems pick up pamphlets.

270
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:14,460
Help my mother clear the table.

271
00:32:19,180 --> 00:32:21,296
May I take your plate now?

272
00:32:21,700 --> 00:32:25,329
-Yes, the fine's spoiled my appetite.
-We'll sort it out.

273
00:32:25,980 --> 00:32:27,538
Thank you, Raoul.

274
00:32:28,980 --> 00:32:31,289
-Excuse her.
-Where are you going?

275
00:32:31,500 --> 00:32:33,456
What's happening?

276
00:32:34,460 --> 00:32:36,178
Come back for the table.

277
00:32:40,940 --> 00:32:43,693
Make an an effort, dear.

278
00:32:53,660 --> 00:32:55,571
You don't understand.

279
00:32:56,580 --> 00:32:58,457
There's a war on.

280
00:33:43,700 --> 00:33:45,099
You're very beautiful..

281
00:33:57,020 --> 00:33:58,089
-do you know her?
-Yes.

282
00:33:58,300 --> 00:34:03,454
Could she wait outside?
I don't want customers seeing a native here.

283
00:34:08,060 --> 00:34:09,129
Raoul!

284
00:34:11,580 --> 00:34:12,729
Nour!

285
00:34:56,820 --> 00:34:59,175
Show me what your Raoul bought you.

286
00:35:01,860 --> 00:35:03,657
It's beautiful!

287
00:35:06,420 --> 00:35:10,254
You're so lucky.  Khaled never buys me anything.

288
00:35:11,460 --> 00:35:13,974
Don't worry,
He'll buy you presents one day.

289
00:35:13,975 --> 00:35:14,975
We'll see.

290
00:35:17,860 --> 00:35:21,773
-He still hasn't found work?
-It's hard right now.

291
00:35:24,100 --> 00:35:26,216
It's hard for us too.

292
00:35:38,020 --> 00:35:39,658
-Here, you have it.
-No keep it.

293
00:35:40,140 --> 00:35:41,892
-Take it
-No, it's a gift.

294
00:35:42,100 --> 00:35:43,658
Please, take it.

295
00:35:44,700 --> 00:35:46,099
What about Raoul?

296
00:35:46,580 --> 00:35:48,571
I'll say I lost it.

297
00:35:48,900 --> 00:35:51,937
-He won't believe you.
-He will, don't worry.

298
00:35:53,220 --> 00:35:56,451
What about me?
What do I tell Khaled?

299
00:35:57,740 --> 00:35:59,298
I don't know.

300
00:36:02,700 --> 00:36:04,258
Say you found it.

301
00:36:05,540 --> 00:36:08,771
Found it while collecting some pamphlets.

302
00:36:13,580 --> 00:36:15,013
That's true.

303
00:36:19,900 --> 00:36:22,095
Can I ask you something?

304
00:36:23,140 --> 00:36:24,459
Yes.

305
00:36:25,420 --> 00:36:27,376
I'd like to see Khaled again.

306
00:36:31,860 --> 00:36:33,293
All right.

307
00:36:50,340 --> 00:36:53,571
Don't worry,
I'll get myself a pass.

308
00:36:53,780 --> 00:36:55,850
-You can?
-Yes.

309
00:36:56,060 --> 00:36:59,848
And I'll even get work.
and money.

310
00:37:00,060 --> 00:37:03,894
- Have you told my father?
- No, not yet.

311
00:37:06,980 --> 00:37:08,459
Does March suit you?

312
00:37:08,660 --> 00:37:10,969
- For what?
- Our wedding.

313
00:37:33,580 --> 00:37:36,777
Your eyes, your lips...

314
00:37:39,540 --> 00:37:42,179
Come here.
- No.

315
00:37:49,100 --> 00:37:52,888
- I've been waiting for years.
- Like everyone.

316
00:37:53,100 --> 00:37:56,172
Let me, please.

317
00:37:56,780 --> 00:37:59,135
I beg you, my love.

318
00:38:00,140 --> 00:38:02,608
-Don't you love me anymore?
-Yes. I love you.

319
00:38:03,420 --> 00:38:05,012
Forgive me.

320
00:38:19,750 --> 00:38:23,030
-Tell me about
when you first saw me..

321
00:38:23,031 --> 00:38:25,031
I already told you.

322
00:38:25,032 --> 00:38:27,032
Tell me again.

323
00:38:28,800 --> 00:38:30,615
-Come on tell me.

324
00:38:36,300 --> 00:38:39,400
As soon as I saw you,
I knew you were the one.

325
00:38:39,401 --> 00:38:41,128
And then?

326
00:38:42,300 --> 00:38:44,700
Then, my father told me

327
00:38:44,720 --> 00:38:47,060
you were the cousin I'd marry.

328
00:38:47,061 --> 00:38:49,121
But I already knew it was you.

329
00:38:49,122 --> 00:38:51,122
How do you know?

330
00:38:51,123 --> 00:38:54,469
-I was trembling.
-And now?

331
00:38:54,480 --> 00:38:59,570
-Yes.

332
00:38:59,600 --> 00:39:01,618
Don't be afraid.

333
00:39:52,420 --> 00:39:53,819
Here I am.

334
00:39:57,940 --> 00:39:59,293
What are you doing?

335
00:40:05,540 --> 00:40:06,973
Who is that?

336
00:40:08,740 --> 00:40:10,571
Who is that, Myriam?

337
00:40:13,020 --> 00:40:14,658
Have you done it?

338
00:40:20,660 --> 00:40:23,094
My God,
my daughter is a slut!

339
00:40:25,740 --> 00:40:29,528
-What will I tell Raoul now?
-I don't want to  marry him.

340
00:40:29,900 --> 00:40:31,049
Shut up!

341
00:40:31,260 --> 00:40:33,654
If your father was alive,
he'd slap your face!

342
00:40:33,720 --> 00:40:35,619
He'd never marry me
to a man I hate!

343
00:40:35,980 --> 00:40:37,777
Shut up, you whore!

344
00:40:53,220 --> 00:40:56,576
Seen this?  It's all spoiled.

345
00:41:01,420 --> 00:41:03,331
I'll buy you another one.

346
00:41:07,180 --> 00:41:09,410
When do you start work?

347
00:41:12,620 --> 00:41:14,258
I don't know.

348
00:41:20,940 --> 00:41:23,454
Tomorrow,
I have to go to the "Kommandantur".

349
00:41:26,740 --> 00:41:28,890
You're working for the Germans?

350
00:41:29,180 --> 00:41:30,659
Yes.

351
00:41:31,540 --> 00:41:33,656
They're decent people.

352
00:41:34,180 --> 00:41:36,740
They've promised us independence
after the war.

353
00:41:38,420 --> 00:41:40,172
I didn't know that.

354
00:41:41,780 --> 00:41:44,533
There are a lot of things
you don't know.

355
00:41:53,260 --> 00:41:54,932
I'll teach you.

356
00:42:01,180 --> 00:42:02,613
Who is he?

357
00:42:12,700 --> 00:42:15,533
-What did you do with him?
-Everything.

358
00:42:21,100 --> 00:42:22,533
Meaning?

359
00:42:23,540 --> 00:42:26,930
Everything. He lay down on me,
blew in my mouth and..

360
00:42:33,260 --> 00:42:34,978
Ah Myriam...

361
00:42:45,380 --> 00:42:48,531
Give this to your mother,
for the wedding expenses.

362
00:43:11,660 --> 00:43:15,016
-Well?
-I've sorted it out.

363
00:43:15,220 --> 00:43:17,017
Thank you, you've saved us.

364
00:43:18,140 --> 00:43:20,495
There's no problem.
Everything is fine.

365
00:43:22,260 --> 00:43:24,091
No problem, Tita!

366
00:43:28,900 --> 00:43:32,688
I forgot to ask you
for the wedding night...

367
00:43:33,860 --> 00:43:37,139
Do you want the bride
Oriental or European style?

368
00:43:37,355 --> 00:43:38,855
Oriental...

369
00:43:42,370 --> 00:43:43,870
Oriental.

370
00:44:36,660 --> 00:44:39,811
Be brave, you have to be beautiful
for your wedding night.

371
00:44:43,550 --> 00:44:46,214
How did it go with Khaled
the other night?

372
00:44:46,600 --> 00:44:50,290
-He found work!
-What kind of work?

373
00:44:51,100 --> 00:44:52,818
He didn't say.

374
00:44:54,420 --> 00:44:55,899
Stand up!

375
00:45:09,700 --> 00:45:12,596
I have a friend
whose jealous neighbour

376
00:45:12,700 --> 00:45:14,700
wanted her fiance.

377
00:45:15,100 --> 00:45:17,710
On the wedding night
she cast a spell:

378
00:45:17,911 --> 00:45:20,011
and she became like a baby!

379
00:45:23,240 --> 00:45:27,015
Didn't the father kill her
when he saw the unstained sheet?

380
00:45:27,020 --> 00:45:30,610
The poor man lived with the shame
all his life!

381
00:45:30,620 --> 00:45:35,138
-Which family was it?
-The whole neighborhood knows!

382
00:45:35,340 --> 00:45:37,251
I know who it is.

383
00:46:01,540 --> 00:46:05,215
You have to be clean
to please your husband.

384
00:46:05,420 --> 00:46:07,058
Don't be afraid.

385
00:46:30,940 --> 00:46:34,376
Your husband
wants you as soft as silk.

386
00:47:03,820 --> 00:47:05,731
It's all right, it's all right.

387
00:47:12,380 --> 00:47:14,655
Relax, the pain will pass.

388
00:47:37,600 --> 00:47:39,592
Everything's fine.

389
00:48:00,300 --> 00:48:02,012
You see, your skin is silky.

390
00:48:15,220 --> 00:48:16,858
There, it's all over.

391
00:48:46,100 --> 00:48:49,100
I have to tell her and show her.

392
00:49:10,250 --> 00:49:11,750
Answer!

393
00:49:12,271 --> 00:49:14,499
Where are your children?
Your husband?

394
00:49:14,500 --> 00:49:17,011
I don't know,
I don't understand French.

395
00:49:17,300 --> 00:49:19,915
-What did she say?
-She doesn't speak French.

396
00:49:20,000 --> 00:49:23,266
For hostages,
it's best to take men.

397
00:49:23,640 --> 00:49:26,379
Where's her family?

398
00:49:26,700 --> 00:49:29,176
There's no one else.  My husband is dead

399
00:49:29,200 --> 00:49:30,939
and  my daughter's married.

400
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:35,736
-She  lives alone.
-Is that true?

401
00:49:35,737 --> 00:49:36,737
No, she has a daughter.

402
00:49:39,000 --> 00:49:42,034
But she isn't home from school yet.

403
00:49:42,900 --> 00:49:44,160
I beg you...

404
00:49:44,176 --> 00:49:47,699
I've done nothing,
I've paid the fine, I...

405
00:49:47,700 --> 00:49:49,700
-We'll come back.

406
00:49:52,100 --> 00:49:55,133
What do we do?
Search the place

407
00:49:55,540 --> 00:49:58,934
Take the jewels,
money and sewing machine.

408
00:49:59,300 --> 00:50:01,894
-There's nothing.
-They hide everything.

409
00:52:49,500 --> 00:52:51,377
Bitch!

410
00:52:55,760 --> 00:52:57,739
Good morning, Myriam, everything well?

411
00:52:58,500 --> 00:53:00,138
Good morning.

412
00:53:01,260 --> 00:53:02,613
Everything well?

413
00:53:03,060 --> 00:53:04,459
Everything well.

414
00:53:06,060 --> 00:53:09,530
What's wrong with her?
I don't understand.

415
00:53:10,020 --> 00:53:12,250
God only knows, my daughter.

416
00:53:26,060 --> 00:53:29,018
-What are doing here?
-Nothing.

417
00:53:31,500 --> 00:53:34,014
Why did you pick
those leaflets up on the square?

418
00:53:34,220 --> 00:53:35,778
I was curious.

419
00:53:41,740 --> 00:53:45,528
Has Khaled told you about his work?
No.

420
00:53:46,540 --> 00:53:48,735
-Nothing?
-No.

421
00:53:50,300 --> 00:53:52,338
He came to our place
with the Germans and French.

422
00:53:53,540 --> 00:53:56,771
They stole from us
and hurt my mother.

423
00:53:57,080 --> 00:53:59,336
-He did wrong nothing.
-I saw him with them

424
00:53:59,340 --> 00:54:01,296
-It wasn't him!
-I saw him.

425
00:54:01,700 --> 00:54:05,932
You saw wrong.
What do you have against Khaled?

426
00:54:07,300 --> 00:54:08,892
Are you jealous?
No.

427
00:54:14,460 --> 00:54:16,576
I'd rather die than live your life.

428
00:54:16,980 --> 00:54:19,289
You know nothing
about what I'm going through.

429
00:55:19,606 --> 00:55:23,606
<i>...An office will be opened
at the high school.</i>

430
00:55:24,700 --> 00:55:27,300
<i> And now a final reminder.</i>

431
00:55:27,301 --> 00:55:29,701
<i> In application
of Colonel Rauf's decision</i>

432
00:55:29,802 --> 00:55:32,302
<i> and in accordance with
the bill posted in the city,</i>

433
00:55:33,300 --> 00:55:38,698
<i> German authorities require 
a contingent of 2,000 Jewish workers</i>

434
00:55:38,700 --> 00:55:43,655
<i>for excavation work
 and trench digging.</i>

435
00:55:43,700 --> 00:55:46,700
<i>All able bodied Jewish men
 must be presented tomorrow</i>

436
00:55:48,132 --> 00:55:49,332
Raoul!

437
00:55:49,140 --> 00:55:51,700
<i>to the 08:00 of the morning</i>

438
00:55:51,900 --> 00:55:54,653
<i>in the Jewish workers recruitment center</i>

439
00:55:55,020 --> 00:55:57,056
<i> with shovels and a picks.</i>

440
00:55:57,260 --> 00:56:01,094
<i>No Jewish inhabitant is</i>

441
00:56:01,300 --> 00:56:03,097
<i>exempt of that obligation. ..</i>

442
00:56:24,064 --> 00:56:25,807
Shalom Hajaj.

443
00:56:29,660 --> 00:56:31,935
-Age?
-Thirty years.

444
00:56:32,340 --> 00:56:35,093
-Profession?
-Locksmith.

445
00:56:35,300 --> 00:56:38,497
-Any health problems?
-I cough a lot.

446
00:56:38,700 --> 00:56:40,292
Come hear.

447
00:56:41,640 --> 00:56:43,219
Cough!

448
00:56:44,220 --> 00:56:45,220
Again

449
00:56:46,077 --> 00:56:47,321
That way.

450
00:56:52,287 --> 00:56:54,213
Felix Haddad!

451
00:56:56,940 --> 00:56:59,500
-Age?
-Fifty.

452
00:57:00,740 --> 00:57:03,174
-Profession?
-Doctor.

453
00:57:04,600 --> 00:57:07,692
I know you.  You're a carpenter.
Not a doctor.

454
00:57:08,490 --> 00:57:10,332
You damn traitor!

455
00:57:20,042 --> 00:57:24,017
-Traitor!
- You're not a man!

456
00:57:48,220 --> 00:57:51,053
If I'd been in their shoes,
I'd have spat in your face too.

457
00:57:52,460 --> 00:57:54,769
I wasn't my  decision
to send only the poor.

458
00:57:54,980 --> 00:57:56,618
You're an accomplice.

459
00:58:00,400 --> 00:58:02,856
Who's decision was it?

460
00:58:04,436 --> 00:58:07,000
The community leaders.  

461
00:58:07,003 --> 00:58:10,218
 We had orders to protect the elite.

462
00:58:12,838 --> 00:58:14,652
That's horrible.

463
00:58:16,160 --> 00:58:17,978
What can I do?

464
00:58:25,040 --> 00:58:26,898
Resign.

465
00:58:26,900 --> 00:58:29,734
If I do, I'll be sent away too.

466
00:58:33,000 --> 00:58:35,370
They'll need doctors there.

467
00:58:40,600 --> 00:58:42,577
You really want that?

468
00:58:45,200 --> 00:58:47,894
I don't want my fiance
to be called a coward.

469
00:58:53,500 --> 00:58:56,169
Know why I chose you
at the synagogue?

470
00:58:56,400 --> 00:58:57,934
No.

471
00:58:59,360 --> 00:59:01,692
For what you did at school.

472
00:59:02,300 --> 00:59:05,093
I  wanted to help you.

473
01:00:28,161 --> 01:00:29,409
Where's this bra from?

474
01:00:30,060 --> 01:00:31,652
It's new.

475
01:00:32,190 --> 01:00:35,314
Where did you get the money for it?

476
01:00:35,390 --> 01:00:37,415
It was a present.

477
01:00:37,680 --> 01:00:39,219
Who from?

478
01:00:39,220 --> 01:00:40,220
Why do you want to know?

479
01:00:39,660 --> 01:00:43,209
You mustn't wear
another girl's clothes!

480
01:00:43,420 --> 01:00:44,648
We're not beggars.

481
01:00:44,860 --> 01:00:47,328
-Who gave it to you?
-A woman.

482
01:00:47,540 --> 01:00:49,212
A woman? Who?

483
01:00:52,660 --> 01:00:54,013
Myriam?

484
01:00:54,560 --> 01:00:55,937
Take it off!

485
01:00:55,939 --> 01:00:57,938
-Why?
Take it off!

486
01:00:58,100 --> 01:01:01,010
You don't need to dress
like a whore to please me!

487
01:01:01,011 --> 01:01:02,957
Take it off!

488
01:01:33,300 --> 01:01:35,730
You mustn't see Myriam again.

489
01:01:37,500 --> 01:01:38,993
Yes.

490
01:01:39,177 --> 01:01:40,894
All right.

491
01:01:45,060 --> 01:01:49,099
<i>The bride 
has blackened her eyelashes</i>

492
01:01:50,020 --> 01:01:55,890
<i>And made up her lips.
She has been to the hammam</i>

493
01:01:56,100 --> 01:02:02,016
<i>And hennaed her hair.
she has on her most beautiful dress</i>

494
01:02:02,220 --> 01:02:05,132
<i>and all her bracelets</i>

495
01:02:05,340 --> 01:02:08,696
<i>but she is still missing something</i>

496
01:02:09,100 --> 01:02:10,215
<i>What is it?</i>

497
01:02:10,420 --> 01:02:12,376
<i> Her ring.
-No.</i>

498
01:02:37,660 --> 01:02:39,093
Give me a son.

499
01:02:45,700 --> 01:02:47,898
I want a son when I get back...

500
01:03:11,790 --> 01:03:13,219
Here.

501
01:03:14,050 --> 01:03:15,932
Get dressed.

502
01:03:30,040 --> 01:03:32,376
We'll talk about it when I get back.

503
01:03:34,370 --> 01:03:36,053
Thank you.

504
01:03:40,100 --> 01:03:42,336
Have you packed  my things?

505
01:03:55,260 --> 01:03:57,172
I've put in some food too.

506
01:03:57,110 --> 01:03:58,673
Thank you.

507
01:04:03,350 --> 01:04:04,960
I should go.

508
01:04:06,730 --> 01:04:09,091
Your father's waiting outside.

509
01:04:10,000 --> 01:04:11,699
I know.

510
01:04:29,170 --> 01:04:30,799
-Raoul!

511
01:04:30,800 --> 01:04:32,354
Yes?

512
01:04:32,400 --> 01:04:34,133
Don't go.

513
01:04:35,190 --> 01:04:37,178
It's too late now.

514
01:06:43,700 --> 01:06:47,228
Don't worry, Oum Khaled.
My daughter is in good health.

515
01:06:47,980 --> 01:06:50,376
She looks a bit skinny to me.

516
01:06:50,660 --> 01:06:52,550
Here's your's money.

517
01:06:52,552 --> 01:06:57,373
Better late than never.

518
01:06:59,020 --> 01:07:00,670
Go on in.

519
01:07:19,770 --> 01:07:21,999
Inspection!  No one leaves!

520
01:07:22,100 --> 01:07:24,809
Men aren't allowed in here now!

521
01:07:25,180 --> 01:07:26,435
Stay here!

522
01:07:28,010 --> 01:07:29,274
-She has no veil.

523
01:07:29,275 --> 01:07:31,275
-They respect nothing.

524
01:07:36,320 --> 01:07:37,249
-Catch them!

525
01:07:37,250 --> 01:07:39,770
-They're hiding in the steam bath!

526
01:08:10,140 --> 01:08:12,098
She's my sister.  A Moslem.

